Harry Love (30 May 1871 – 26 March 1942) was an English cricketer.  Love was a right-handed batsman who bowled right-arm slow-medium.  He was born at Hastings, Sussex.
Love made his first-class debut for Sussex against Cambridge University in 1893.  He made four further first-class appearances for the county, the last of which came against the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1894.  In his five first-class matches, he had ten batting innings, scoring a total of 110 runs at an average of 12.22, with a high score of 33.He died at Ore, Sussex on 26 March 1942.
